## üéØ Research Foundation (40+ Academic Sources)

### Neurodivergent Cognition
- Oxford 2025: Cognitive profiles (ADHD = creativity + divergent thinking; Autism = visual-spatial + pattern recognition; Dyslexia = big-picture perspective)[6]
- NIH 2023: Meta-analysis showing autistic individuals excel at reasoning but show reduced processing speed; ADHD shows mostly typical performance with working memory reduction[9]
- Nature 2024: Visual processing differences in autism and dyslexia linked to reduced motion sensitivity but enhanced spatial attention[13]

### Programming Language Design
- Plankalk√ºl analysis: Explicit types, 2D notation, mathematical clarity[1][2][4][5]
- Brainfuck: Extreme minimalism (8 ops) enables mastery despite complexity[7][10]
- Befunge: 2D spatial execution spawned entire "Fungeoid" language family for spatial thinkers[21][22][24]
- Whitespace: Pattern-based syntax demonstrates minimalism works[26][29]

### Error Design & UX
- Context-aware errors reduce cognitive load (ArXiv 2025)[31][32][33]
- Cognitive Load Theory: Vague errors force mental effort; context-guided messages support recovery[31]
- Progressive disclosure: Complexity on-demand prevents overwhelm[37]

### AI Integration Architecture
- Multi-model orchestration (IEEE 2025): Specialized models outperform single general models[16]
- Semantic context protocols: Different models need different context formats[19]
- Transparent reasoning: Users trust AI more when they understand why[31]

### Accessibility Standards
- WCAG 2.2 AAA: Contrast, timing, navigation, authentication[17][20]
- W3C Neurodiversity Guidelines: Sensory control, predictability, cognitive support[17][20]
- Participatory design: Include neurodivergent users as co-creators[27][30]

